From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] power: supply: qpnp-smb5: wire dynamic boost to
 flash_active

Call schgm_flash_set_active() when POWER_SUPPLY_PROP_FLASH_ACTIVE is
set by the camera HAL.  This engages the 5V boost while the torch LED
is on and releases it when the torch turns off, allowing adaptive USB
charging to resume.

Signed-off-by: Kent <kent@build.local>
---
 drivers/power/supply/qcom/qpnp-smb5.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/power/supply/qcom/qpnp-smb5.c b/drivers/power/supply/qcom/qpnp-smb5.c
index abcdef1..1234567 100644
--- a/drivers/power/supply/qcom/qpnp-smb5.c
+++ b/drivers/power/supply/qcom/qpnp-smb5.c
@@ -1448,6 +1448,12 @@ static int smb5_property_set(struct power_supply *psy,
 	case POWER_SUPPLY_PROP_FLASH_ACTIVE:
 		if ((chg->chg_param.smb_version == PMI632_SUBTYPE)
 				&& (chg->flash_active != val->intval)) {
+			/*
+			 * Dynamic boost: engage 5V boost while torch is on,
+			 * release when torch turns off to resume charging.
+			 */
+			schgm_flash_set_active(chg, val->intval);
+
 			chg->flash_active = val->intval;
 
 			rc = smblib_get_prop_usb_present(chg, &pval);
-- 
